{
  "stem": "719.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I used to get every two weeks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But what was so interesting-- my father had a sister in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That's the one that later on, I found and went to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This sister was in hiding.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Belgian gentiles made a-- bless their heart.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They weren't as mean!",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I don't know why-- why.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I'm not saying all the Poles-- because I-- I met very nice Pollacks too.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But they were so jealous of the Jews that wherever they saw a Jew, they were reporting.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "My uncle, my aunt survived in hiding.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "He risked his life to go to the post office to [NON-ENGLISH], to send a package to me, to camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the post office knew that he's Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She pretends she doesn't know him-- Mr.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Gold, my uncle.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I told my aunt and uncle after the war that God gave them a lot of years, because they-- that's how I survived.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "That's how they helped me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I have a picture here of them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "There is one picture.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "My uncle-- my father, actually, my father wrote to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Every two weeks, I was allowed to write a few words.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And this is only until 1943.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Then everything stopped, because they took all the Jews, and they didn't want us to know what happened to our family.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So their last postcard-- I think I have it on there-- came back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "No more Jews.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We'd-- I mean, we'd-- we were hoping they're alive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "But nobody knew.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "They closed mail.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So from 1942 to '43, which is a whole year-- working.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I'll explain what we were doing, what was the production.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Since we had little fingers, this was a factory that produced spools of thread, raw thread-- not polished, not black, but raw, like greenish color from flax.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
